---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="About">
  <section class="section container">
    <div class="about-layout">
      <div class="prose">
      <p class="eyebrow">cat about.md</p>
      <h1>About</h1>
      <p>
      I am a computational biology researcher interested in applying genomics, machine learning, and bioinformatics to understand human disease. I was drawn to bioinformatics because it combines analytical problem-solving with biology, allowing computational methods to answer questions with real clinical impact. Although I had never programmed before university, I became fascinated by the role of computation in biology, taught myself to code, and ultimately pursued a minor in Computer Science alongside my specialist in Bioinformatics and Computational Biology.
      <br></br>
      My research has centered on building computational tools and reproducible analysis pipelines for large-scale genomic datasets. Through projects spanning gene regulatory networks, evolutionary genomics, bulk and single-cell RNA sequencing, I have developed a strong foundation in statistical genomics and biological data analysis. I am currently a Computational Biology Researcher at the Ontario Institute for Cancer Research (OICR), where I use single-cell transcriptomics to investigate the developmental origins of medulloblastoma, a pediatric brain cancer.
      <br></br>
      More broadly, I am motivated by the potential of machine learning to transform biology and medicine. I am particularly interested in developing computational methods that integrate genomics and AI to improve our understanding of cancer and enable more precise diagnosis and treatment. I plan to pursue graduate studies in computational biology, with the long-term goal of translating advances in data science into meaningful improvements in human health.
      </p>
      <p>
  
     <h3>Research Interests</h3>

     <ul>
      <li>Computational Genomics</li>
      <li>Machine Learning for Biology</li>
      <li>Single-Cell & Spatial Omics</li>
      <li>Sequence-to-Function Models</li>
      <li>Cancer Genomics & Brain Tumours</li>
      <li>Precision Medicine</li>
      <li>Tumour & Phenotype Characterization</li>
      <li>Stem Cell Biology</li>
      <li>Antibody Engineering</li>

      </ul>

      <h3>Education</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong> Honours Bachelor of Science (HBSc), University of Toronto (2022 - 2026) </strong>
        <br>
        Specialist in Bioinformatics and Computational Biology with minors in Computer Science and Immunology </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

  <div class="about-image">
      <img src="/images/headshot.png" alt="Tanaya Datar" />
    </div>

  </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
